00059 // Forward declare the context typedef so that we can use it before it is
00060 // properly defined. Delegators and delegates (from import statements) are
00061 // interdependent and their context structures contain pointers to each other
00062 // C only allows such things to be declared if you pre-declare the typedef.
00063 //
00064 typedef struct wswdLexer_Ctx_struct wswdLexer, * pwswdLexer;

00069 // Disable: Unreferenced parameter,                                                     - Rules with parameters that are not used
00070 //          constant conditional,                                                       - ANTLR realizes that a prediction is always true (synpred usually)
00071 //          initialized but unused variable                                     - tree rewrite variables declared but not needed
00072 //          Unreferenced local variable                                         - lexer rule declares but does not always use _type
00073 //          potentially unitialized variable used                       - retval always returned from a rule 
00074 //                      unreferenced local function has been removed    - susually getTokenNames or freeScope, they can go without warnigns
00075 //
00076 // These are only really displayed at warning level /W4 but that is the code ideal I am aiming at
00077 // and the codegen must generate some of these warnings by necessity, apart from 4100, which is
00078 // usually generated when a parser rule is given a parameter that it does not use. Mostly though
00079 // this is a matter of orthogonality hence I disable that one.
00080 //
00081 #pragma warning( disable : 4100 )
00082 #pragma warning( disable : 4101 )
00083 #pragma warning( disable : 4127 )
00084 #pragma warning( disable : 4189 )
00085 #pragma warning( disable : 4505 )
00086 #endif
